ch_dataset: Dataset broker/server
=================================



Installing ``ch_dataset``
-------------------------

To get ``ch_dataset``, use git to clone the repository::

	$ git clone git@bitbucket.org:chime/ch_dataset.git  # add the ``-b`` option to specify a branch

Create a clean python environment. You can make a new one with:

	$ virtualenv my_env  # create new virtual environment

or clear an existing one with:

	$ virtualenv --clear my_env  # clean an existing virtual environment

Install the ``ch_dataset`` package, whill will fetch and install all dependencies::  

	$ pip install -e ./ch_dataset  # install all dependencies. -e makes it editable in-place.


System requirements
-------------------

There are no specific system requirements

Development
-----------

The code that was cloned can be edited directly and pushed back to the git server.

If some dependency needs to be edited, it should be uninstalled (``pip uninstall ...```), cloned locally, and pip install -e shall be run on that clone.
